unday, August 4.\n\nArmenian Artur Davtyan won the silver medal and Britain’s Harry Hepworth took the bronze at the Bercy Arena.\n\nThe 24-year-old Yulo won his second gold medal in as many days after he became the first Filipino to capture an Olympic gymnastics title on thefloor exerciseon Saturday, August 3.\n\nHere’s a look at the Filipino superstar’s historic moment:\n\n– Rappler.com\n\nHow does this make you feel?\n\nfollow us\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n", "title": "IN PHOTOS: Gymnastics star Carlos Yulo scoops historic 2nd Olympic gold", "top-image": "https://www.rappler.com/tachyon/2024/08/reuters-carlos-yulo-podium-paris-olympics-2024-scaled.jpg", "domain": "www.rappler.com", "lang": "en-US", "author": "Jasmine Payo", "description": "Gymnast Carlos Yulo pulls off what no other Filipino athlete has done – capture two Olympic gold medals", "keywords": ""}